content:
After you add widgets to a dashboard, optimize it for viewing on smaller screens. For example, remove widgets from a layout for on-the-go mobile users, and rearrange widgets for users with tablet-sized screens.

When you generate a new layout, widgets from the currently selected layout can be automatically added to the new layout or you can add widgets manually. If the current layout contains multiple pages, CRM Analytics also copies the pages to the new layout.

To create a layout, click Add Layout and choose other layout properties such as grid settings, background color, and device specifications. The designer updates the preview in real time so that you can see how your changes affect the display.

You can set the layout name, add unused widgets, apply a background image, or specify themes to create aesthetic properties for dashboard widgets all at once. To save your layout changes, save the dashboard.

Layout properties specify the layout name, designer grid settings, background settings, and requirements for devices that can use this layout. If multiple layouts are defined for a dashboard, CRM Analytics chooses the optimal layout when displaying the dashboard on a device based on device properties specified for each layout.
title: Customizing CRM Analytics Dashboards
